.TH "rpmsg_trysendto" 9 "rpmsg_trysendto" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpmsg_trysendto \- send a message across to the remote processor, specify dst
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rpmsg_trysendto
.BI "(struct rpmsg_endpoint *ept "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "u32 dst "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ept" 12
the rpmsg endpoint
.IP "data" 12
payload of message
.IP "len" 12
length of payload
.IP "dst" 12
destination address
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function sends \fIdata\fP of length \fIlen\fP to the remote \fIdst\fP address.
The message will be sent to the remote processor which the \fIept\fP
endpoint belongs to, using \fIept\fP's address as source.
In case there are no TX buffers available, the function will immediately
return -ENOMEM without waiting until one becomes available.

Can only be called from process context (for now).

Returns 0 on success and an appropriate error value on failure.
